Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.88,0:03:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So quantum mechanics then takes us into the world of the fuzzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.91,0:04:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the Newtonian paradigm, you see, here's the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.91,0:04:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the limitation of the mechanistic reductionist
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.06,0:04:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,who is stuck with a computational, limited, permanent, constricted, settled, sequential,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.06,0:04:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,provable, highly predictable world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.51,0:04:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, although he believes in that, he doesn't live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.51,0:04:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives farther to the right in the quantum potential,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.51,0:04:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the quantum potential, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.51,0:04:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because in actuality, subjectively, things are quite disorderly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not at all predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They're quite illogical, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.51,0:04:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're creative, they're actually free.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.51,0:04:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not determined.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.73,0:04:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A little bit of imagination totally changes the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.73,0:04:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's progressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.76,0:05:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are not separate and discrete and therefore measurable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.76,0:05:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,without defining context
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.89,0:05:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're intermingled and interconnected.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.89,0:05:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They're diffuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.72,0:05:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The accident that happened with, what do you call that thing that was off in the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.72,0:05:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Space shuttle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.72,0:05:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Space shuttle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.20,0:05:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.38,0:05:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not within the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.86,0:05:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the carelessness, the indifference, the somewhatness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.86,0:05:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the, oh yeah, of humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.86,0:05:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.86,0:05:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.86,0:05:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times have you taken off in your car
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.92,0:05:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you really should have checked the pressure in your left rear tire
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.92,0:05:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you didn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.92,0:05:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.92,0:05:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.92,0:05:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It drove me back and forth to work all week.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, that's not measurable, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.33,0:05:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Caringness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's diffuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.72,0:05:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's vague.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.72,0:06:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-local.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.61,0:06:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Things happen that are beyond comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.96,0:06:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Things don't happen separate from each other but simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.08,0:06:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,These things here are measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,These things here are observable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can measure a quantum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.24,0:06:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But how would you measure, is it worth the bother or not
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to check the pressure in the rear tire?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it worth the bother?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.24,0:06:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not immeasurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.24,0:06:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, your lip just hung in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.24,0:06:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Your lip hangs in the balance by, oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we could.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.24,0:06:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'd rather have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.34,0:06:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of lives just went down the soup there, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.88,0:07:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine the time of invasion of, I'm not very left-brained today,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.52,0:07:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the great invasion of Germany across the English Channel,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.74,0:07:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Britain and Normandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.77,0:07:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And who was the German general?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.77,0:07:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Rommel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.77,0:07:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Rommel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.80,0:07:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Rommel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.80,0:07:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Rommel was off celebrating his wife's birthday
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,on the day of the great invasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.80,0:07:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which the Allies likely would not have won had Rommel been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.96,0:07:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But Rommel said, okay, Christina, or whatever his name is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.48,0:07:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he didn't want to disappoint his wife, so he wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.67,0:07:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Any more than the admirals were available in Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.67,0:07:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They were off at a party someplace, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.15,0:07:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.15,0:07:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Where were the great admirals?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.28,0:07:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The great admirals to defend Pearl Harbor on December 7th, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.28,0:08:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they were at a birthday party or someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.28,0:08:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are the non-ponderables, the immeasurables.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are the things that define, decide human history, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.28,0:08:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The human history is not decided by the Maginot Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.28,0:08:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Maginot Line in World War II was indestructible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.28,0:08:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing could have gotten across the Maginot Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if I was the general on this side,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.56,0:08:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have said, I will put up a Maginot Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That forces them to come across through the Ardennes Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.56,0:08:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would have been waiting for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.66,0:08:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And wouldn't have been surprised at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.66,0:08:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So history then is set by the imponderables.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.42,0:08:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Just fleeting mood, a slight forgetfulness, a little bit of tiredness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You get something in your eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.11,0:08:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.11,0:08:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's altered by observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.11,0:09:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the whole quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.11,0:09:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's altered by observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.72,0:09:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody interested in explanation of the quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.72,0:09:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it applies to consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.72,0:09:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.72,0:09:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.72,0:09:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we will show that after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.72,0:09:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's expansive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.72,0:09:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with context.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.72,0:09:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So the field then is context.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.29,0:09:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is the world of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian paradigm is the world of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.29,0:09:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Force goes from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.64,0:09:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And consequently, it expends energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.77,0:09:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, it results in counter force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.77,0:09:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Force always results in counter force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.09,0:09:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Force always exhausts itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.09,0:09:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The great Roman Empire dominated for a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.83,0:09:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, it couldn't be fit anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.83,0:09:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, gold, bodies, lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.83,0:09:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And it just petered out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.83,0:10:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They just married the local women and the empire dissolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It just petered out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.83,0:10:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The heck with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.83,0:10:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It killed so many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.83,0:10:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He just pooped from killing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.83,0:10:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And he just falls over and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.83,0:10:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.83,0:10:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll get married and raise kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.83,0:10:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the end of the Roman Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.81,0:10:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, power is like gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.81,0:10:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Power, which is like spirituality,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.53,0:10:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,influences everything within its field
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.53,0:10:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequent of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.76,0:10:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequent of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritually devoted people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.95,0:10:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,think that they're bringing about change in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.95,0:10:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,by doing this and doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.95,0:10:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with doing this and doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.95,0:10:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.95,0:11:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What you have become then empowers the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.95,0:11:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The field then brings about
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.95,0:11:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,certain consequences automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.52,0:11:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.52,0:11:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So power does not consume energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.52,0:11:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to feed anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.52,0:11:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,any energy to gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.75,0:11:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Gravity just completely controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.75,0:11:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It influences everything within its domain
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.42,0:11:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and it requires no power at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.42,0:11:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not consume power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.77,0:11:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So divinity then encompasses all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.77,0:11:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And its power is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And like a great gravitational field,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.00,0:11:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,everything within it then
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.00,0:11:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is at the effect of the power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.25,0:11:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why divine justice is absolute,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.20,0:11:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal and absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.20,0:11:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of the power and the quality
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.20,0:12:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the nature of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.16,0:12:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point of fearing God
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.16,0:12:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because the giant electromagnet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.32,0:12:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw out behind this building this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.32,0:12:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,every little iron filing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.32,0:12:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely told by the power
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.76,0:12:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of the magnetic power then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.01,0:12:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are all subject to divine justice
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.16,0:12:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which is absolutely perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.16,0:12:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and not arbitrary or capricious
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.16,0:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or vengeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.80,0:12:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't require all the things
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.80,0:12:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that have been alluded to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.80,0:12:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the source of all power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.83,0:12:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's poised.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.21,0:12:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it resides in the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the quantum reality then is subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.00,0:12:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's skip that one
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.32,0:13:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead we'll go to the left-hand side of the folder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.32,0:13:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I think at the back we've got...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.32,0:13:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren't going to do quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.32,0:13:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but if they want quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.38,0:13:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,by God, they're going to get quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.38,0:13:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.48,0:13:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're going to hear what I know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.48,0:13:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to show this one
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.53,0:13:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.30,0:13:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the name of that guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.23,0:13:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the morphogenetic...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.23,0:13:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rupert Sheldrake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.23,0:13:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rupert Sheldrake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.23,0:13:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not very left-brained today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.23,0:13:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rupert Sheldrake's morphogenetic fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.23,0:13:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how the pattern within consciousness then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.23,0:13:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,manifests in what appears to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.26,0:13:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the out-picturing of ABC.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.39,0:13:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The sequence...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.39,0:13:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is actually just perception, see,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.39,0:13:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because you grasp first this,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.35,0:13:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,grasp this, then you grasp this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.35,0:13:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So you think it's happening that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.35,0:13:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're perceiving it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.35,0:13:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The way it is, is ABC, like a gestalt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.35,0:13:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It then displays itself in the world suchly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.35,0:14:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.35,0:14:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.18,0:14:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we weren't going to do this one
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.20,0:14:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because it gets us off into left brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.75,0:14:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll bless left brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.75,0:14:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless left brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.75,0:14:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And get right on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.75,0:14:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And go right in, yeah, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.75,0:14:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So for those that like it, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.75,0:14:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,on the internet there's a fellow named Henry Stapp.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.75,0:14:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,S-T-A-P-P.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.84,0:14:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor of Advanced Theoretical Physics at Berkeley.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.84,0:14:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And his program on the internet
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably the best I know of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.84,0:14:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to make quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.84,0:14:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it would apply to spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.84,0:14:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehensible to the ordinary mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.20,0:14:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have an ordinary mind as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.20,0:14:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,an extraordinary mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.23,0:14:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this came out in 1927.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.23,0:14:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the Schrodinger, famous Schrodinger equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.23,0:14:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two Schrodinger equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.23,0:14:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One's time dependent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.23,0:14:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The other is time independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.23,0:15:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to go into its mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.23,0:15:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I purposely left off the mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.23,0:15:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But the quantum state of a system then is its potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.42,0:15:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Heisenberg process is where choice and intention
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.42,0:15:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and decision come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.48,0:15:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there can be no karmic responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.55,0:15:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,no evolution if it weren't for choice and possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.55,0:15:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So intentionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.55,0:15:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So karma is set by spiritual intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.41,0:15:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of intention is what sets one's spiritual karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.41,0:15:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the act but the intention behind the act.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.41,0:15:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So intentionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.41,0:15:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So Heisenberg observation, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.41,0:15:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was on the submicroscopic level
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.60,0:15:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that you cannot do the same example twice
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.60,0:15:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because having looked at it, you've already changed it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.60,0:15:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is no longer the same example.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.67,0:15:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg process introduces choice
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.67,0:15:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and intention and consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.67,0:16:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness enters in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.67,0:16:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Dirac process is what happens after you observe it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.66,0:16:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,or make a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.66,0:16:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's called the collapse of the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.66,0:16:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the universe has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.66,0:16:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's changed because you've looked at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.66,0:16:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've decided something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.69,0:16:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the process by which this happens
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.69,0:16:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,was described by von Neumann as process two,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.69,0:16:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.69,0:16:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Process one, the mental.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.98,0:16:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you see here, the universe can only say,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.98,0:16:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what we said this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.17,0:16:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the universe, according to quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.17,0:16:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,can only say yes or not yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.17,0:16:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot say no.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.43,0:16:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the kinesiologic response then
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.43,0:16:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is explicable by quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.94,0:16:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the thing is, and if it is, your arm goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.00,0:16:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is not, your arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.00,0:16:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But it cannot say yes or no.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.00,0:16:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only say yes or not yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.00,0:16:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I ask your arm, this is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.45,0:16:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I do it by making a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.45,0:17:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't ask a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.52,0:17:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We can say, this is an adequate description
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.52,0:17:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of what I just got through explaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.52,0:17:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an adequate description of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.52,0:17:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an adequate description of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.61,0:17:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual decision and choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.16,0:17:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how we evolve spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.32,0:17:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So the collapse of the wave function
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.85,0:17:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,takes it from a potentiality to an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.85,0:17:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And in so doing, we fulfill our karmic evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.08,0:17:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.08,0:17:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can go on to the sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.69,0:17:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To this point of view, from this point of view,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.04,0:17:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of this, whatever is talking now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.04,0:17:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it talks by itself, by the way, just like it moves by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.04,0:17:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.24,0:18:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees this world, human world,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.24,0:18:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as a purgatorial realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.68,0:18:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Purgatorial in that human beings suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.68,0:18:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Human beings have the opportunity to undo old bad karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.00,0:18:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the opportunity to create new karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.00,0:18:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Purgatorial in that it offers the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.32,0:18:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from the most base and hideous of human behaviors and choices
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.32,0:18:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the most lofty and exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.32,0:18:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're going to sacrifice others
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.73,0:18:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to your personal ends,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.73,0:18:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or sacrifice your personal ends
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.73,0:18:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to the welfare of others out of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.98,0:18:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is a huge choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.98,0:18:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the karmic consequences are quite profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.98,0:18:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to evolve, then, we would have,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.98,0:18:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and to also be answerable for who we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.98,0:18:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have to have a universe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.98,0:18:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is purgatorial in range of option.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.98,0:19:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If this was just heavenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.40,0:19:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was nothing but goodness,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.40,0:19:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and all you had was good options
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.40,0:19:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about good people coming from good persons,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing things goodly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you're stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.62,0:19:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.62,0:19:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're stuck in heaven, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.62,0:19:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.14,0:19:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We observed this morning that everybody is born
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.14,0:19:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with a different calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.14,0:19:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, life as we see it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.27,0:19:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,within this domain is evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.27,0:19:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Its expression has been evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.43,0:19:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And the individual consciousness is evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.43,0:19:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you need a realm of optimal opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.43,0:19:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Optimal opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.07,0:19:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Optimal opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.35,0:19:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking today at lunch
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.35,0:19:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,about how people get over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.35,0:20:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Viewed from that viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.67,0:20:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then, war is really a necessity, isn't it, almost, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.67,0:20:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you going to undo the karma
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.86,0:20:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the people that you've killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.86,0:20:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you get killed yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.86,0:20:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,One way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.79,0:20:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get beyond 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.79,0:20:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the masculine domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.98,0:20:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you do it by walking into a hail of bullets
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.98,0:20:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of the queen,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.98,0:20:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of the throne,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.98,0:20:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.98,0:20:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of your country,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.98,0:20:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of your comrades,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.98,0:20:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of your regiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.98,0:20:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For something greater than yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.98,0:20:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you're willing to surrender your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.33,0:20:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That takes you above 200 forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.00,0:20:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's in the masculine domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.00,0:20:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to win because you're going to get the ribbon,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.80,0:20:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but because you're doing it for the university.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're using it for the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.80,0:20:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Women athletes do it for womanhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.80,0:20:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Men do it for whatever they may be doing it for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.09,0:21:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're run by testosterone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.09,0:21:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The victims, there's real victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.32,0:21:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That testosterone loses on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.99,0:21:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and you got what you can see out there as history.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.99,0:21:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The way the traditional masculine way to cross over.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.33,0:21:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, why do wars keep recurring all that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.33,0:21:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In some ways, there's no way beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.33,0:21:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only when, for the good of the regiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.81,0:21:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you walk shoulder to shoulder
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.81,0:21:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and walk right knowingly into a hail of bullets,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.81,0:21:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're willing to die for your country,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.81,0:21:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,your flag, for your family, for your wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.45,0:21:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,for womanhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.45,0:21:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the man does.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.22,0:21:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.22,0:21:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For a higher purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.98,0:21:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You shoot above 200 forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.58,0:21:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman does the same thing in childbirth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.58,0:22:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of bullets, childbirth threatens her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.58,0:22:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the centuries, she died by the millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.64,0:22:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The average woman died sooner or later of childbirth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.03,0:22:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She had three or four children and then died.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.80,0:22:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If she got as far as three or four.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.89,0:22:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And I looked through the old bible of my own family,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.89,0:22:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's the pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.89,0:22:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She had little Ricky, she had little Jimmy,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.89,0:22:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and then she died when in childbirth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.89,0:22:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And the man at that time was on his third wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.89,0:22:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,First two had died in childbirth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.89,0:22:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one's pregnant, God help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.08,0:22:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,For the sake of bringing forth new life,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.08,0:22:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the woman passes over the likelihood of death
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.56,0:22:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and faces death as a distinct possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.56,0:22:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And she shoots above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.56,0:22:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The paradigm then is a little bit different.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.56,0:22:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the calibrated levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.98,0:22:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We went up as far as 600, I think, on that other scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.98,0:22:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because 600, you enter a different dominion,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.98,0:23:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a different domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.98,0:23:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.98,0:23:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You transcend identification with the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.98,0:23:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you begin to identify as the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.49,0:23:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, you don't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.49,0:23:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.49,0:23:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, one is blissed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.49,0:23:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And all thought stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.49,0:23:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The process usually stops at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.55,0:23:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually stops at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.55,0:23:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually stops at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.55,0:23:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually stops at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.55,0:23:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually stops at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.55,0:23:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually stops at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.28,0:23:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He walks and talks almost like a real human.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.28,0:24:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He's very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.35,0:24:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get over 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.51,0:24:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God help you if you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.51,0:24:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, 600 is enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.89,0:24:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A very profound experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.89,0:24:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Happens 1 in 10 million human lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.89,0:24:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Extremely profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.89,0:24:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of the people leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.89,0:24:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like luck,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.65,0:24:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if it happens within your own experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.65,0:24:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that somebody may come along
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and see to it that you get off the rock
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.97,0:24:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and eat something, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.97,0:24:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because by 700, again,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.04,0:24:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of Ramana Maharshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.04,0:24:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance, is quite typical.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.04,0:24:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you've ever been in that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.07,0:24:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.07,0:24:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He stopped eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.16,0:24:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't talk for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.16,0:24:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They found him in a bliss-out state.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.16,0:24:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He was covered with bugs and bugs and sores
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.16,0:24:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and been nibbled on by mice and various things.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.36,0:24:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But he had spiritual friends who discovered him
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.36,0:25:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and nurtured him and got him back to eating
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.61,0:25:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and various things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.61,0:25:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But he did not speak for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.61,0:25:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're into serious spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.22,0:25:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.22,0:25:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're into serious spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.73,0:25:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody around should know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.76,0:25:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Your friends, your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.82,0:25:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for the continuation of your physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.82,0:25:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.82,0:25:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you topple over or not
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.82,0:25:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is really not of any particular importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.82,0:25:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But they might haul you to a psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.95,0:25:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whose decision is to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.11,0:25:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're catatonic
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.11,0:25:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and need shock treatment or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.11,0:25:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramana Maharshi would have been taken to a psychiatrist,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.17,0:25:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't he, if he was doing that today?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.17,0:25:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Silent, not talking,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.17,0:25:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,seemed out of this world, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.17,0:25:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I was a consultant to Zen monasteries
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.72,0:26:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've been consulting the Catholic diocese,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.72,0:26:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Epictetus diocese, Zen monasteries,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.72,0:26:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.72,0:26:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that was my job,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.10,0:26:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to differentiate between true spiritual states,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.10,0:26:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and pathologic psychiatric disorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.20,0:26:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this religious ecstasy?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.20,0:26:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is this manic depressive psychosis
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.26,0:26:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and into religious delusions,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.26,0:26:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, grandiose delusions?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.26,0:26:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a while I get a letter
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.84,0:26:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,from somebody that's in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.84,0:26:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They just discovered they're God
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.84,0:26:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and want to share the information.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.84,0:26:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I tell them, if you were God,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.84,0:26:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't be interested in sharing the information,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.84,0:26:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.84,0:26:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But the mere fact that you asked me
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.12,0:26:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,shows that it's not likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.12,0:26:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I think in chapter 10 of the last book,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.61,0:26:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we had an audience like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.61,0:26:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We went over the attributes of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.68,0:26:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as they really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.71,0:27:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And we had 100% unanimity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.51,0:27:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We divided it up into ones and twos.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.51,0:27:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole crowd of us did it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.51,0:27:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at Creative Life Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.92,0:27:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think we listed about 18 of the qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.92,0:27:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the actual qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.92,0:27:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the qualities of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.28,0:27:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's using the term qualities lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.28,0:27:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.28,0:27:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answers were unanimous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.28,0:27:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Unanimous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.43,0:27:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you calibrate them,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.43,0:27:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy fields of God is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.43,0:27:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,God manifests as divinity or creator is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.52,0:27:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we have other things that we have read about
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.52,0:27:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.07,0:27:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Within this domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.07,0:27:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,within this domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.07,0:27:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest calibrated level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.07,0:27:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,compatible with walking around on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.07,0:27:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is about a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.10,0:27:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason for that appears to be
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.29,0:27:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that the human nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.29,0:28:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot really handle anything over a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.29,0:28:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It hasn't up until recent times,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.29,0:28:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think it's evolving
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.29,0:28:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's going to be able to handle 1250.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.29,0:28:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But anything over 6 to 700 is already painful
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.52,0:28:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and it feels like you're being slowly electrocuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.52,0:28:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.96,0:28:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that he felt as though his bones were broken and cracked.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.96,0:28:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He said his bones were broken and cracked.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.03,0:28:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He tried the same thing, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.03,0:28:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt as though his bones were cracked and broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.67,0:28:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.67,0:28:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Christ, Buddha, Krishna, Brahman,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.86,0:28:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,all one thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.86,0:28:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Avatar, 985.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.86,0:28:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Self as beyond existence or non-existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.40,0:28:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we said at age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.40,0:28:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the confrontation
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.47,0:28:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,at about 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.47,0:28:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality as allness or nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.82,0:28:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Self as beyond existence or non-existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.82,0:29:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend that duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.14,0:29:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a teacher of enlightenment, 800.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.24,0:29:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I as sage, 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.24,0:29:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment, 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.62,0:29:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the other scale went up to 600
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.62,0:29:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it stopped there,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.62,0:29:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you wonder what's beyond 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.88,0:29:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.88,0:29:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that pretty much covers it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.51,0:29:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.51,0:29:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When you said over 600, 50% leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.51,0:29:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there, 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.51,0:29:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean die?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.51,0:29:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The physicality, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.51,0:29:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, to leave the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.51,0:29:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's no interest in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.51,0:29:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,By choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.31,0:29:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not a realm of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.31,0:29:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very hard to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.86,0:29:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence becomes overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.04,0:29:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And one has,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.04,0:29:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,implicit and part and parcel
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.04,0:29:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence is permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.04,0:30:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a knowingness within the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.80,0:30:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have permission to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.80,0:30:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be walking down the aisle
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.12,0:30:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of a lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.12,0:30:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it becomes all of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.12,0:30:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,very intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.38,0:30:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost like a magnetic attraction to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.38,0:30:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You have complete permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.38,0:30:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.38,0:30:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have permission to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.63,0:30:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know whether
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.63,0:30:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the physicality will continue or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.63,0:30:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened right during a lecture one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.63,0:30:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And other people know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.63,0:30:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The audience didn't know
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.63,0:30:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it was going to continue
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.63,0:30:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with the body or not either.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.88,0:30:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It just came out of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.88,0:30:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the attraction to leave the body
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.88,0:30:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,was quite intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.88,0:30:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the permission was quite,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.88,0:30:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,quite overt.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.14,0:30:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was no way,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.14,0:30:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it was, the witness watched to see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.14,0:30:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,if the body was going to make it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.14,0:30:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to the end of the aisle and back or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.14,0:30:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.14,0:30:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the way it went then.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.14,0:30:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It just comes out of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.49,0:31:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You were talking about your own experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.75,0:31:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this was, yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.75,0:31:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that was a personal experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.75,0:31:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When it first came out,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.75,0:31:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.75,0:31:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,One can leave or not leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.75,0:31:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And my presumption was
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.10,0:31:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is some karmic propensity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.41,0:31:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or some decision prior made
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.41,0:31:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that's running it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.41,0:31:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a personal decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.41,0:31:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But if some purpose is served
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.41,0:31:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,by the continuation,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.41,0:31:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it may be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.41,0:31:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It may go that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.41,0:31:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's no,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.41,0:31:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no inner self
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.41,0:31:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,saying yes or no to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.41,0:31:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there was only the witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.48,0:31:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the body would continue
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.48,0:31:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to walk down the aisle
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.48,0:31:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and make it back again
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.48,0:31:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or it wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.48,0:31:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no way of knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.48,0:31:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that similar to 1938
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.48,0:31:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when you were in the snow bank?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.48,0:31:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.48,0:31:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes, in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.48,0:31:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who've had near-death experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.48,0:31:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget, there were some here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.48,0:31:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.64,0:31:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.64,0:31:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,very characteristic about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.64,0:32:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the difference between
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.64,0:32:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,out-of-body and near-death
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.64,0:32:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is that without a body,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.64,0:32:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in out-of-body there's no change
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.64,0:32:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of calibrated level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.64,0:32:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quite surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.70,0:32:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because here you think
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.02,0:32:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.02,0:32:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You think your name is Dave.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.02,0:32:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're laying in this bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.02,0:32:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly you're 12 feet away
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.02,0:32:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,from the body looking down here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.02,0:32:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and the you is up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.02,0:32:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The you is up here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.02,0:32:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and if thought moves
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.02,0:32:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,over this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.02,0:32:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the entity or whatever it is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.02,0:32:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,moves over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.45,0:32:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You would think after
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.45,0:32:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,such an experience
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.45,0:32:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that at least the realization
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.45,0:32:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm not a physical body
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.45,0:32:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,would bring about a shift
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.45,0:32:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.45,0:32:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But surprisingly it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.45,0:32:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Out-of-body for some reason
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.45,0:32:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,does not bring
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.45,0:32:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a shift of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.45,0:32:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Near-death experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.93,0:32:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.93,0:32:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.93,0:32:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Near-death experience
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.06,0:32:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is much more profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.06,0:32:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which was
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.06,0:33:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you think you are
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.06,0:33:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is replaced by a presence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.06,0:33:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite love,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.06,0:33:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,stillness, security,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.16,0:33:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that has always been.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.44,0:33:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One realizes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.44,0:33:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that that's who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.44,0:33:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That that who I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.18,0:33:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.08,0:33:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,existed before all universes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.08,0:33:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and will exist after all universes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.08,0:33:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.27,0:33:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,After all universes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.27,0:33:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have sprung forth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.27,0:33:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as a breath out of Indra,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.27,0:33:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dream
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.27,0:33:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,has sucked them back in,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.27,0:33:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I am will prevail.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.27,0:33:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The certainty then
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.16,0:33:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.44,0:33:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people think
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.44,0:33:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that the death is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.44,0:33:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.44,0:33:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because of love for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.57,0:33:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,there may be a decision
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.57,0:33:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to re-breathe the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.57,0:33:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no necessity
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.57,0:33:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to re-breathe the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.57,0:33:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And my advice is don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.73,0:34:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.73,0:34:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if your father thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.73,0:34:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've died
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.73,0:34:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because he believes in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.99,0:34:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I see my father sitting there
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.99,0:34:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and he believes in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.15,0:34:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you don't re-breathe the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.15,0:34:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,he's going to think you died
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.15,0:34:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's going to go through grief
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.15,0:34:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and all such.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.15,0:34:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite apparent in that state
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.22,0:34:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.22,0:34:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So the other good news this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.60,0:34:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or this afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.60,0:34:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is that death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.60,0:34:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.98,0:34:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.98,0:34:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.98,0:34:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the law of conservation of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.98,0:34:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the law of conservation of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.98,0:34:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the law of conservation of matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.98,0:34:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and because that's the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.98,0:34:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they forgot the more important paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.98,0:34:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the law of the conservation of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.98,0:34:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot extinguish life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.98,0:35:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Life can go from one form into another,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.04,0:35:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot extinguish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.04,0:35:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.46,0:35:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if a moth is flying by and you swat it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.46,0:35:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the moth goes right on flying
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.49,0:35:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's an etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.49,0:35:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't even notice the change.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.49,0:35:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes right on flying along
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.00,0:35:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's an etheric body
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.00,0:35:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it comes back after a while
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.00,0:35:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,through an egg and all that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.00,0:35:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and comes back
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.00,0:35:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and has another physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.00,0:35:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Swat that and it doesn't even notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.00,0:35:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.07,0:35:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A moth doesn't even notice it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.19,0:35:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,if you swat it out of its physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.19,0:35:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't even notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.67,0:35:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you killed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't kill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.80,0:35:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.80,0:35:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you kill it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.80,0:35:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is the essence of existence
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.80,0:35:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is beyond the swat,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.89,0:35:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.89,0:35:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't kill its electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.89,0:35:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't kill anything about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.89,0:35:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but you did knock it out of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.89,0:35:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you feel guilty that you've killed something
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.96,0:35:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you go into lifetimes of penance,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.96,0:36:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things you've killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.96,0:36:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when you haven't killed anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.96,0:36:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If life was killable,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.96,0:36:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,none of us would be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.24,0:36:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is hardly everybody in this audience's first lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.24,0:36:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody gets to an audience this advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.24,0:36:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in their first lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.24,0:36:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If life was killable,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.24,0:36:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be nobody here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.24,0:36:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.32,0:36:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask if there are people here
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.76,0:36:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in their first karmic lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.76,0:36:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There are.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.96,0:36:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's here in their first karmic lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.08,0:36:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no newly born spirits amongst us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.08,0:36:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is indestructible.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.30,0:36:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of the conservation of the energy of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.30,0:36:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,far more important than the conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.36,0:37:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.42,0:37:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can force it from one form into another form,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.77,0:37:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot kill life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.80,0:37:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible to kill life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.93,0:37:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the near-death experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.96,0:37:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that is a realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.96,0:37:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious that you are, before,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.96,0:37:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.96,0:37:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you are before this universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.96,0:37:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I was before this universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.30,0:37:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will still be here
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.30,0:37:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,after this universe had disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.30,0:37:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a statement of fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.09,0:37:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a statement of fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.12,0:37:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It came on as a realization
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.12,0:37:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was 12 years old in a snowbank.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.12,0:37:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One's immortality is obvious
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.43,0:37:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because the essence of the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.43,0:37:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of the source of your own existence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.43,0:37:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.43,0:37:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how could you be separated
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.52,0:37:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,from your own essence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.52,0:37:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.61,0:38:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.74,0:38:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, after a near-death experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.74,0:38:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a curious loss of fear of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.74,0:38:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,which I didn't know about
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.93,0:38:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,until a few years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.93,0:38:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But, experientially,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.93,0:38:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,all fear of death disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.93,0:38:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.93,0:38:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,when people were blowing up
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.06,0:38:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and people were throwing up with fear, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.06,0:38:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there wasn't the slightest even concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.06,0:38:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there'd be a mind
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.06,0:38:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,ready to go off right next to the ship
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.06,0:38:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and the horns of this mind
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.06,0:38:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,would be bumping against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.06,0:38:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody would swat with fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.06,0:38:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.06,0:38:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,look, keep that guy away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.06,0:38:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only concerned with the job
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.06,0:38:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of keeping that thing from bumping us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.06,0:38:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you could blow up
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.06,0:38:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,never even crossed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.35,0:38:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there was a peculiar loss of fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.35,0:38:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Death has lost its possibility as a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.35,0:38:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, an oncoming bullet or something
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.35,0:38:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't bother you at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.35,0:38:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't want the shooter
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.35,0:38:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to feel guilty that he killed you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.35,0:38:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because, you know, it's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.35,0:39:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.35,0:39:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you're enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.35,0:39:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and somebody's going to assassinate you,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.35,0:39:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.35,0:39:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You go,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.35,0:39:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate loud noses, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.35,0:39:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate loud noises.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.35,0:39:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He's doing what he thinks he's got to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.48,0:39:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, God bless him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.48,0:39:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.48,0:39:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if he does it for a holler or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.48,0:39:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.48,0:39:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that takes care of near death.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.28,0:39:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Near death experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.50,0:39:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Transformative.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.50,0:39:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.50,0:39:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,before and after a near death experience
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.50,0:39:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.50,0:39:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.50,0:39:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,many people have remarked about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.50,0:39:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctors have written about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.50,0:39:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,People who survive heart attacks
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.50,0:39:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,will tell you their life is transformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.50,0:39:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All the materialistic goals they had before
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.50,0:39:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,now seem ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.50,0:39:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The love of,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.85,0:39:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,love then becomes the predominant motif.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.65,0:39:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.65,0:39:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,gone through double,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.65,0:39:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,triple bypass
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.65,0:40:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and near death of cardiac arrest,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.36,0:40:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,usually are quite a bit different
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.36,0:40:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when they survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.36,0:40:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless they're imbeciles.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.96,0:40:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here trans,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.96,0:40:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,survived cardiac arrest
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.96,0:40:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or major cardiac events?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.09,0:40:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.09,0:40:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a pretty young audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.09,0:40:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.09,0:40:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But any of those who have
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.09,0:40:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,know that life is profoundly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.09,0:40:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.99,0:40:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trying to transcend the mind then.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.47,0:40:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If the mind is the big block,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.47,0:40:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.47,0:40:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 435,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.47,0:40:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.47,0:40:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is the ultimate block.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.47,0:40:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got the spiritual motivation,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.47,0:40:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got the know-how,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.47,0:40:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got all the books,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.47,0:40:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the teachers, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.47,0:40:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the thing that intervenes then
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.47,0:40:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is thinkingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.47,0:40:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And the problem then
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.47,0:40:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is how to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.47,0:40:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the identification with the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.47,0:40:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.40,0:40:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which is pretty sophisticated,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.40,0:40:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we already know we're not the,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.40,0:40:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we know we're not the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.40,0:41:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That we're pretty certain about.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.40,0:41:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you take off your arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.40,0:41:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.40,0:41:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take off this arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.40,0:41:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.40,0:41:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take off this leg,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.40,0:41:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.40,0:41:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take off this leg,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.40,0:41:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.40,0:41:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You take off an ear,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.40,0:41:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you take off a thumb,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.40,0:41:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what you take off,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.40,0:41:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you still say I.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.40,0:41:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you get,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.40,0:41:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't be the physical body,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.40,0:41:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or I'd only feel like half my eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.40,0:41:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,half an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.40,0:41:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.40,0:41:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If my thumb went to heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.40,0:41:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.40,0:41:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I'm less of an eye
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.40,0:41:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,than I used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.40,0:41:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.40,0:41:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He's waiting for me over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.40,0:41:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me back my thumb, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.52,0:41:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.75,0:41:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care of that karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.75,0:41:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.75,0:41:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I stuck my thumb in your eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.75,0:41:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.75,0:41:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.75,0:41:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.12,0:41:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.12,0:41:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.12,0:41:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in contemplation and meditation then,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.12,0:41:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll notice that there are fields
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.12,0:41:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and levels of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.12,0:41:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, you're aware of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.22,0:41:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's content.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.22,0:41:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.22,0:41:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,structure and form.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.22,0:41:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what people complain about
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.22,0:42:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,when they go to try meditating.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.22,0:42:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.22,0:42:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get my mind to stop
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.22,0:42:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,creating pictures, images, memories
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.22,0:42:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that whole tantasmagoria.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.22,0:42:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you watch the rise and fall
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.72,0:42:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the content of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.72,0:42:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty soon you become aware
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.72,0:42:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're not the content
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.72,0:42:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because the content is constantly flowing by
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.72,0:42:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,like a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.72,0:42:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead, what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.72,0:42:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is the witness, the watcher.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.72,0:42:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, identification is not
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.91,0:42:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with the content of consciousness now,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.91,0:42:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but the witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.10,0:42:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the witness and the recognizing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.10,0:42:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or the observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.92,0:42:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.92,0:42:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is witnessing the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.92,0:42:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, instead of identifying
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.92,0:42:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with the content of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.92,0:42:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you become aware
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.92,0:42:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.92,0:42:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.92,0:42:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the watcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.92,0:42:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.92,0:42:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.00,0:43:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Gadatta Maharaj
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.00,0:43:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,became enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.36,0:43:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,after only not too many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.87,0:43:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And the teaching of his guru
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.87,0:43:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,was to watch the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.22,0:43:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And Mr. Gadatta,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.22,0:43:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrated about 720 or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.22,0:43:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the same as Ramana Maharshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.22,0:43:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,taught people to really watch the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.59,0:43:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what he was saying was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.91,0:43:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,focus on,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.04,0:43:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,focus up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.04,0:43:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't focus on content of mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.04,0:43:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,focus the watcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.04,0:43:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the watcher, the witness of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.04,0:43:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you begin to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.13,0:43:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that watching and witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.13,0:43:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.13,0:43:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not deciding to witness and watch
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.13,0:43:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what goes on in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.13,0:43:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an impersonal phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.13,0:43:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you identify with the content of mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.00,0:43:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you think it's personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.00,0:43:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you realize,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.00,0:43:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how could it be personal?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.00,0:43:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you don't have any choice
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.00,0:44:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,whether to witness and watch
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.00,0:44:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what's going on in the content of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.00,0:44:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.25,0:44:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't take credit for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.25,0:44:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither should you take this credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.25,0:44:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one quality,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.25,0:44:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,now you begin to notice
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.25,0:44:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the impersonal qualities of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.25,0:44:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It automatically witnesses and watches
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.25,0:44:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and automatically registers
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.25,0:44:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is a phenomenon coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.25,0:44:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of a quality of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.25,0:44:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.80,0:44:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the unmanifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.12,0:44:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the unmanifest becomes the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.12,0:44:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest is the Godhead,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.82,0:44:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes manifest as divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.82,0:44:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the allness of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.82,0:44:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is created,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.30,0:44:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,both visible and invisible,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.30,0:44:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of the unmanifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.30,0:44:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming manifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.30,0:44:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,radiates out as the light of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.30,0:44:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the source of all life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.20,0:44:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.20,0:44:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason you can't kill life
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.20,0:45:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is because you can't kill God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.80,0:45:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought that you could kill life
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.80,0:45:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,would mean that you could kill a part of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.80,0:45:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.85,0:45:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we can stop feeling guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.85,0:45:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,about all the little ants we stepped on.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.85,0:45:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's a certain point
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.85,0:45:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.85,0:45:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,where you feel guilty about every ant
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.85,0:45:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that you might have stepped on.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.85,0:45:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It is some sort of a semi-Buddhist tradition
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.85,0:45:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.98,0:45:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they wear mosquito nettings
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.98,0:45:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so they won't breathe any bacteria in their mosquitoes
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.98,0:45:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and accidentally kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.27,0:45:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They must be doing some karma there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.46,0:45:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go on next.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.46,0:45:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,From carelessness about life,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.46,0:45:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,now one becomes overly protective about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.46,0:45:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.26,0:45:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.51,0:45:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.51,0:45:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it's the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.51,0:45:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see on the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.51,0:45:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see the list on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.57,0:46:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me we're missing something
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.92,0:46:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we wanted to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.92,0:46:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.92,0:46:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need a picture anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.56,0:46:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.56,0:46:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me just see the list,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.56,0:46:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the typed list.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.56,0:46:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.56,0:46:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.56,0:46:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.63,0:46:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,all the ones I brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.63,0:46:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes, we did, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.63,0:46:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's just go through
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.82,0:46:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the application of calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.82,0:46:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world that we look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.82,0:46:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.91,0:46:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The calibrated levels of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.06,0:46:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are a profound implication.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.06,0:46:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We mentioned this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.25,0:46:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the application of spiritual principles in business.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.25,0:46:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We gave Walmart as an example,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.60,0:46:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating at around 350,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.60,0:46:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of integrity in business.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.60,0:46:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity in business is not airy-fairy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.80,0:46:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows up on the bottom line
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.80,0:46:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as the biggest corporation
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.80,0:46:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and most successful corporation in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.12,0:46:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.12,0:46:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is application of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.12,0:47:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We've done a lot of research
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.12,0:47:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating the levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.12,0:47:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the world of spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.12,0:47:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,over great periods of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.12,0:47:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Gitas,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.12,0:47:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,where they calibrate ancient Hindu Vedas
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.12,0:47:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 900s,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.12,0:47:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way down to current writers, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.15,0:47:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,One application that we ran across
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.15,0:47:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the 9-11 and the recent events
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.15,0:47:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was to calibrate the regions of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.34,0:47:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So people are following
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.34,0:47:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and demonstrating karmic patterns.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.34,0:47:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like great cycles of people
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.34,0:47:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who come in and come in together.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.40,0:47:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We see North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.40,0:47:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we say our group was here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.40,0:47:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,435, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.40,0:47:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this group is 435.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.63,0:47:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the higher you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.63,0:47:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the more high it is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.63,0:47:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.63,0:47:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,logarithmic progression.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.82,0:47:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So 400 is not twice 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.88,0:47:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's immensely more than 200
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.88,0:48:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's the log of 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.01,0:48:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so 421 is America today.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.01,0:48:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,415, 410 is North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.17,0:48:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, Mexico is 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.17,0:48:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's still so.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.17,0:48:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me it should be higher than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.17,0:48:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mexico is over 255, 260.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.17,0:48:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's still 255. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.24,0:48:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then we go into the Caribbean islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.24,0:48:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We go into middle America.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.13,0:48:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that it's in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.13,0:48:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So throughout...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.13,0:48:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the high 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.64,0:48:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you go on down and you're in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.64,0:48:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The 300s are still extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.64,0:48:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,300s are a very high energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.77,0:48:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lot of ambition,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.77,0:48:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.77,0:48:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of willingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.77,0:48:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that this hemisphere, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.77,0:48:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is potentially a pretty peaceful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.77,0:48:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got 400s and you've got 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.77,0:48:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly in the middle of all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.77,0:48:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if you calibrate all these maps,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.77,0:49:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,your Central America 305,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.77,0:49:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly you see a 55.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.77,0:49:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, turns out to be Haiti.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.02,0:49:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.02,0:49:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, consciousness research,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.02,0:49:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't take any position by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.02,0:49:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, if we use this research
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.02,0:49:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and we begin examining nature, animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.02,0:49:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,geography, populace, civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.02,0:49:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, what kind of a picture will emerge?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.02,0:49:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So we find that here is a whole hemisphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.24,0:49:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely high calorific,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.24,0:49:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,high calibration,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.24,0:49:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and right in the middle of it you have 55.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.37,0:49:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So you just put this in your noodle
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.37,0:49:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand the events of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.37,0:49:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the events of political realities
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.63,0:49:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and what the implication is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.63,0:49:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the implication of 55
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.63,0:49:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of 300s and 400s?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.76,0:49:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that sending,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.76,0:49:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it was tried to send money there
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.76,0:49:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and it made things worse
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.76,0:49:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because it increased nutrition,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.76,0:50:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it created population growth,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.76,0:50:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the poverty got worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.76,0:50:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the question is then,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.76,0:50:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you do with a country that calibrates at 55?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.76,0:50:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it's a completely different question.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.76,0:50:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.37,0:50:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibration of 9-11?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.58,0:50:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.58,0:50:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.58,0:50:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the level of consciousness of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.58,0:50:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,no single event changes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.58,0:50:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,9-11 doesn't change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.58,0:50:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,World War II doesn't change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.58,0:50:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It stayed at 190 after many centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.58,0:50:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,During those centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.58,0:50:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you had the Black Plague,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.58,0:50:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you had the, what was it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.77,0:50:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the Church of the Churches,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.77,0:50:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the Inquisition,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.77,0:50:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you had World War I,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.77,0:50:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you had the Napoleonic Wars,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.77,0:50:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you had mass starvation,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.77,0:50:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you had the great pneumonia,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.70,0:51:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,encephalitis, epidemics after World War I.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.02,0:51:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And none of those things changed
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.02,0:51:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.18,0:51:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we see a more complicated picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.18,0:51:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What we did with one side of the hemisphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.18,0:51:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is this the right sequence?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.18,0:51:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.18,0:51:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.18,0:51:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now if we do this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.18,0:51:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrate all the levels
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.18,0:51:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the countries in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.18,0:51:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what do we find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.18,0:51:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we see Australia, 410.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.18,0:51:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Malaysia, 405.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.18,0:51:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We see India, 355.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.18,0:51:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We see China, 305.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.18,0:51:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Japan and Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.28,0:51:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Korea's about 425 or 430.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.28,0:51:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Mongolia, 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.28,0:51:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So what can we learn from this?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.28,0:51:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the inference, of course, is quite profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.14,0:51:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just merely looking it over,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.14,0:51:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you certainly get a different feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.14,0:51:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for life on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.14,0:51:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it's distributed,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.14,0:51:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what to expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.14,0:52:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The implications for peace is profound
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.48,0:52:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because the implications for government,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.00,0:52:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,politics and economics is profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.00,0:52:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because most countries seem to be completely insensitive
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.96,0:52:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to what is the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.96,0:52:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people they are talking to.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.96,0:52:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you expressing anything in a language
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.96,0:52:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that is even comprehensible or meaningful?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.96,0:52:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk about democracy and freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.47,0:52:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to people who calibrate at 50,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.47,0:52:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they're worrying about whether or not
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.60,0:52:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to survive till tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.60,0:52:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,if they don't have enough food.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.60,0:52:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about voting for somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.60,0:52:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to vote for whoever gives them food,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.60,0:52:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how the drug dealer gains power
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.66,0:52:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,over the neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.66,0:52:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because he becomes the Don.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.66,0:52:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In Chicago, that was historic, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.95,0:52:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So the gangster becomes the hero
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.95,0:52:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're all starving
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.95,0:53:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and he passes out the jobs and the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.95,0:53:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's who you vote for.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.95,0:53:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You vote for somebody that's going to keep you
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.95,0:53:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and your children alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.36,0:53:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you see the implications
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.36,0:53:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for diplomacy, for understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.26,0:53:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you look at each level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.26,0:53:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you go back to the map of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.26,0:53:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to understand human history
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.26,0:53:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in a completely different way
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.26,0:53:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,than you've ever understood it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.52,0:53:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the problems in the world right now
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.52,0:53:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,are coming from North Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.52,0:53:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What are those two countries that are always at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.64,0:53:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Israel and Palestine, where are they up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.64,0:53:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're about 180, 180 to 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.12,0:53:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When people say, I want peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.12,0:53:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and you calibrate there at 180,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.12,0:53:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you know they're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.56,0:53:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because their whole shtick comes out of war, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.56,0:53:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I kill you, then you kill me, then I kill you,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.56,0:53:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then I throw a rocket at you,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.56,0:53:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then I put the fire hose on you, then I bomb you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.56,0:53:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's their whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.01,0:54:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a gun, you're somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.01,0:54:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you get on TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.91,0:54:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,peace is political.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.58,0:54:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't mean peace at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.58,0:54:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.68,0:54:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you want peace, you have peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.68,0:54:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you actually want peace, you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.25,0:54:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have it,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.48,0:54:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because you don't really want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.48,0:54:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just using it as a political slogan
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.48,0:54:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to get votes and justify your political maneuvering.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.64,0:54:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the other thing that calibrating these things does
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.64,0:54:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is unveil the liars in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.64,0:54:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why these lectures are not necessarily popular
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.64,0:54:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in that part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.67,0:54:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When the people think it's the walking god
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.67,0:54:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you calibrate his 180,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.67,0:54:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,can we come down anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.67,0:54:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I just wanted to get Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.67,0:54:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,where I can put my fingers on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.67,0:54:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.67,0:54:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, as low as 50, as low as 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.67,0:54:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,40.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.56,0:54:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's practically a walking death.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.56,0:55:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How they stay alive at 40 is a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.56,0:55:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,70, 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.56,0:55:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you have ongoing civil wars for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.56,0:55:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't just conquer each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.56,0:55:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they slaughter each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.56,0:55:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When this tribe takes this one over,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.56,0:55:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they kill them all and chop them in small pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.56,0:55:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't just kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.56,0:55:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They massacre them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.82,0:55:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you see brutality, starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.82,0:55:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see AIDS ravaging the populace.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.11,0:55:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you look up at Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.00,0:55:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the 400s, the high 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.00,0:55:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at Scandinavia.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.00,0:55:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Spain, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.00,0:55:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,France, all these various countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.20,0:55:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to see the implications for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.20,0:55:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The implications for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.36,0:55:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of attention has to be put where?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.36,0:55:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How to phrase that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.36,0:55:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What is meaningful to people?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.66,0:55:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The holier-than-thou attitude of our government,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.66,0:56:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which antagonizes a good part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.66,0:56:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How should you address the president
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.01,0:56:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of the largest country in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.01,0:56:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that has a culture 6,000 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.24,0:56:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that was civilized for 6,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.24,0:56:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,before your country was even heard of?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.24,0:56:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How should one address such a person?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.40,0:56:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say with respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.81,0:56:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With respect, you might get a positive response.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.81,0:56:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With a superior attitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.84,0:56:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you get non-cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.52,0:56:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the implications for international peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.52,0:56:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,success, and diplomacy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.52,0:56:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of understanding the calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.52,0:56:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of various peoples,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.52,0:56:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the country, the government,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.52,0:56:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ruling regime
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.52,0:56:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.52,0:56:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes the difference between life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.06,0:56:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There are not no such things
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.06,0:56:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as we are talking about this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.06,0:56:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind was ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.06,0:56:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.28,0:57:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom of the ocean is covered
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.28,0:57:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with the skeletons of the dead sailors
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.28,0:57:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.83,0:57:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom of the oceans are covered
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.83,0:57:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,with the wreckage of thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.83,0:57:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and thousands of ships
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.83,0:57:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because they had no compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.05,0:57:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.57,0:57:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.57,0:57:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The cost in lives was enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.57,0:57:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom of the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.57,0:57:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was covered with ships
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.57,0:57:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bodies of brave people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.64,0:57:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,who had no compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.64,0:57:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have a compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.64,0:57:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can no longer claim ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.86,0:57:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No longer claim ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.18,0:57:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's an easier definition
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.18,0:57:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quick to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.18,0:57:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, we see.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.31,0:57:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,These all seem to be safe areas
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.31,0:57:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can address people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.31,0:57:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.82,0:57:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the world of the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.82,0:57:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is for the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.88,0:57:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's reason and logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.88,0:58:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To address people on a different
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.88,0:58:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level with reason and logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.88,0:58:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you sound stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.88,0:58:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You sound stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.95,0:58:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so here you've got,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.04,0:58:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,let me see the world again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.17,0:58:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I just,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.17,0:58:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it's such an easy thing to hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.17,0:58:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but it changes your whole understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.17,0:58:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of the daily newspaper, of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.17,0:58:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of history as recounted by
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.17,0:58:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the political history
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.17,0:58:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and what has gone on
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.17,0:58:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.17,0:58:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we just came back
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.17,0:58:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from two weeks in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.17,0:58:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,where we talked at Oxford University
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.65,0:58:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and we got to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.65,0:58:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like a rerun of history
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.65,0:58:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,from the 1400s, 1500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.16,0:58:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's like a confront
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.16,0:58:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with human history
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.16,0:58:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the Middle Ages
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.16,0:58:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,up until the present time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.39,0:58:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The architecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.39,0:58:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.39,0:58:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and ambiance of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.39,0:58:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is frozen throughout all time
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.39,0:58:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in its sculpture, in its art,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.39,0:59:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in its artistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.68,0:59:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Incredibly impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.68,0:59:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go on to the next one again
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.96,0:59:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll look at the other side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.19,0:59:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.19,0:59:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,after the other side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.19,0:59:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, the application.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.92,0:59:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,See what a profound importance
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.92,0:59:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness research is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.92,0:59:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because you discover things
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.92,0:59:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that nobody's ever known.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.92,0:59:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody in the State Department
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.92,0:59:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,knows anything about what we're talking about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.84,0:59:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.84,0:59:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the most brilliant and experienced heads of government
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.84,0:59:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,know what we all know this instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.84,0:59:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We have already surpassed all governments
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.84,0:59:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and diplomats
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.84,0:59:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of human history.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.84,0:59:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We now know more at one glance
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.84,0:59:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,than they've ever been able to discover
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.84,0:59:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.84,0:59:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the payoff of consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.84,0:59:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So now,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.84,0:59:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we look at the great regions of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.84,0:59:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you bring it down a little bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.84,0:59:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's South Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.84,0:59:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Madagascar.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.84,0:59:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the very dark parts of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.84,1:00:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the dark parts of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.84,1:00:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.84,1:00:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,North Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.84,1:00:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the Near East, the Middle East
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.84,1:00:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,where all the trouble is constantly going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.84,1:00:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you're going to have trouble is
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.84,1:00:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in countries that calibrate 180 to 190
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.84,1:00:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're prideful,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.84,1:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they're into revenge,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.84,1:00:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they're into mutual hatred,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.97,1:00:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're into
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.07,1:00:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,lying, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.07,1:00:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Not telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.07,1:00:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If they were telling the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.07,1:00:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they would calibrate over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.07,1:00:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's fun is to watch the evening news
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.07,1:00:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and watch these world leaders come on
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.07,1:00:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.07,1:00:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives this big thing, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.07,1:00:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, what's the level of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.07,1:00:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of that lecture that he just gave?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.38,1:00:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,180.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.38,1:00:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had world-renowned figures and calibrated them
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.38,1:00:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the entire address
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.38,1:00:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.89,1:00:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,was one lie from the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.89,1:00:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, is there any truth in anything he said
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.89,1:00:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the last half hour?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.89,1:01:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.28,1:01:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,To convincingly lie for half an hour
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.28,1:01:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,non-stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.28,1:01:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's a job requirement.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.85,1:01:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We say Australia should be doing
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.85,1:01:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely well.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.85,1:01:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It is in any way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.85,1:01:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the trouble spots of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.85,1:01:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tailor your expectations then.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.85,1:01:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you sign a contract,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.23,1:01:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only going to be valid
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.23,1:01:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if the other person
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.23,1:01:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,holds the same values
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.23,1:01:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.23,1:01:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't hold the same values,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.23,1:01:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,they think you're stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.74,1:01:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.74,1:01:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to see
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.96,1:01:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the applications of consciousness research
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.96,1:01:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in many areas of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.96,1:01:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how we do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.51,1:01:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.51,1:01:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not exactly ready for publication.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.51,1:01:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all done in pencil.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.51,1:01:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But it took a number of weekends to do all this
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.51,1:01:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and great patience, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.51,1:01:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Over on the upper right hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.64,1:02:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we can pull them down.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.64,1:02:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere we have this typed up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.64,1:02:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This particular one, we didn't get around to typing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.18,1:02:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The trouble spots of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.18,1:02:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We should really try to define
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.18,1:02:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the problem with these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.18,1:02:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.18,1:02:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get their 185, their 165,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.18,1:02:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,their 175, their 160,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.18,1:02:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,180, 185,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.18,1:02:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,190, 180,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.18,1:02:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all less than 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.66,1:02:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you get the turkey,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.66,1:02:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,70 turkeys is over 200, 245.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.66,1:02:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.66,1:02:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we can tailor our expectation
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.66,1:02:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of international relationships,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.66,1:02:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,diplomacy,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.76,1:02:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,our political ideology,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.76,1:02:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to the reality of who these people really are
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.76,1:02:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they see life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.76,1:02:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.76,1:02:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How they see life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.96,1:02:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The world in which I grew up
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.96,1:02:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,saw life in a certain way.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.96,1:02:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The world in which we live now
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.96,1:03:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,sees life in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.31,1:03:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the implications
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.31,1:03:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for human survival?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.27,1:03:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to show you the practical results
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.27,1:03:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.27,1:03:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It completely
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.27,1:03:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,strips illusion
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.27,1:03:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and lays bare
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.56,1:03:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the bonds of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.07,1:03:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you will not find reality and truth
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.07,1:03:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in the daily newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.45,1:03:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find distortions.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.45,1:03:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so let's look at World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.52,1:03:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.93,1:03:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,peace is not something you cause
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.93,1:03:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or create,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.93,1:03:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it's that which you become.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.32,1:03:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace is the automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.32,1:03:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.08,1:03:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Where truth prevails,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.08,1:03:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,peace is automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.08,1:03:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,War is the automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.08,1:03:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.18,1:03:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to peace then
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.18,1:03:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is by insisting on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.34,1:03:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the prevalence of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.34,1:03:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.34,1:04:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to peace then
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.34,1:04:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is through integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.34,1:04:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the dedication and devotion
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.34,1:04:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to God's truth and peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.92,1:04:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So can you bring it down just a little bit?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.92,1:04:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So peace is the natural state
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.92,1:04:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,where truth prevails.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.92,1:04:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,War is the automatic state
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.92,1:04:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when falsehood prevails.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.92,1:04:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the basis of war
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.92,1:04:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.17,1:04:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind has had no basis
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.17,1:04:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.17,1:04:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,so he's not faulted for ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.17,1:04:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Jesus Christ
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.17,1:04:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.91,1:04:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,said there's only one sin
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.91,1:04:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.91,1:04:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Man had no compass to go by,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.91,1:04:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so how answerable is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.91,1:04:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The basis of war, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.91,1:04:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is not evil and awfulness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.93,1:04:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but stupidity and ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.93,1:04:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that so?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.93,1:04:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.93,1:04:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.08,1:04:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The importance of the discovery
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.08,1:04:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of a test to discern truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.08,1:05:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.08,1:05:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is intrinsically designed
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.08,1:05:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and incapable of telling truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.84,1:05:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's convincible.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.10,1:05:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can argue with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.10,1:05:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can persuade it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.10,1:05:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But the mind in and of itself
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.10,1:05:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is like the hardware of a computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.32,1:05:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.32,1:05:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,all the belief systems
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.32,1:05:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are the software.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.32,1:05:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that the hardware
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.32,1:05:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of a computer is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.32,1:05:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can run any software through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.32,1:05:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The hardware remains unsullied.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.32,1:05:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego is the software,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.58,1:05:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is the hardware,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.58,1:05:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.74,1:05:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.74,1:05:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So real spiritual progress
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.96,1:05:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is always based on humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.96,1:05:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The first,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.09,1:05:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,most profound humility
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.09,1:05:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is the acceptance
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.09,1:05:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that the human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.09,1:05:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of itself
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.09,1:06:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is unable to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.05,1:06:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Unable to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.05,1:06:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind can be
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.82,1:06:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,brainwashed into believing anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.82,1:06:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph Gables
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.82,1:06:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was an expert.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.82,1:06:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He could convince you
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.82,1:06:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that black was white.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.82,1:06:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He just kept saying it over.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.82,1:06:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If a lie is repeated often enough,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.82,1:06:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mind will believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.92,1:06:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we as leaders
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.92,1:06:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual truth
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.92,1:06:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have to become aware
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.04,1:06:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that our first humility
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.04,1:06:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is, oh Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.04,1:06:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of itself
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.04,1:06:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.84,1:06:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Human mind cannot discern
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.84,1:06:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.54,1:06:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequence is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.54,1:06:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the inability to discern
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.54,1:06:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,a leader from a megalomaniac.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.54,1:06:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So the history of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.67,1:06:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the last century
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.70,1:06:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,100 million human beings
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.70,1:06:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,have been slaughtered
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.70,1:06:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,by megalomaniacs.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.70,1:07:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How astonishing.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.79,1:07:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,100 million people have died
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.79,1:07:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because they can't tell
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.79,1:07:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a megalomaniac from a leader.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.20,1:07:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be like 100 million people
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.20,1:07:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,dying of poison apples
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.16,1:07:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because they can't discern
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.16,1:07:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a poison apple from a regular apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.16,1:07:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you think a human being
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.16,1:07:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,would know that by now?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.16,1:07:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you watched generation after generation
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.16,1:07:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and hundreds of millions of people die,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.84,1:07:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,people would begin to say
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.84,1:07:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,how can we tell a leader from a maniac?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.48,1:07:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Inability to discern a leader
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.48,1:07:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from a megalomaniac.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.82,1:07:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.82,1:07:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego gets easily,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.82,1:07:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its ignorance,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.82,1:07:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,polarized into ego positions,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.82,1:07:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,distortion of truth and propaganda.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.82,1:07:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The cost to mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.64,1:07:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is death and destruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.64,1:07:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.64,1:07:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if we have now something
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.64,1:08:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that reveals the absolute truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.64,1:08:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what if we go back over history
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.64,1:08:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and examine something,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.64,1:08:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I just picked this one
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.64,1:08:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I knew all the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.84,1:08:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we look
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.84,1:08:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.84,1:08:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,how do all these people calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.84,1:08:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We can look at the Normandy,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.84,1:08:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we can look at all the details
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.84,1:08:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.84,1:08:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with which we're all familiar.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.03,1:08:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We can look at the military
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.03,1:08:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.03,1:08:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we can look at kamikaze pilots
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.03,1:08:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at the lunch hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.03,1:08:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What about a kamikaze pilot?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.03,1:08:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I always see him
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.92,1:08:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as a brave person
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.92,1:08:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,committed to serving
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.92,1:08:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,his emperor and his country
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.92,1:08:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sun god,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.92,1:08:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore a noble.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.92,1:08:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,After World War II,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.12,1:08:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,all the former enemies
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.12,1:08:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,forgave each other
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.12,1:08:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and we all gave recognition
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.50,1:08:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to the warrior,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.50,1:08:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the nobility of the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.79,1:09:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We may have been mistaken,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.79,1:09:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but we may have been mistaken,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.79,1:09:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but our motive was to serve
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.79,1:09:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,god, country, and family.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.79,1:09:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So a kamikaze pilot,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.79,1:09:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we see Adolf Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.79,1:09:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,345.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.79,1:09:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Hirohito
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.79,1:09:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,was right on the edge.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.79,1:09:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Tojo was a little better.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.79,1:09:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto, surprisingly,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.13,1:09:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,was 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.13,1:09:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So these were people
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.13,1:09:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,who were patriotic,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.13,1:09:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated to their country,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.13,1:09:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they believed in their cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.03,1:09:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.03,1:09:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we see Adolf Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.03,1:09:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,45 at the time of his death.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.03,1:09:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Joseph Stalin,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.03,1:09:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,was a wishy-washy guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.03,1:09:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And when Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.03,1:09:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,went to Hitler and got him
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.03,1:09:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to sign a peace treaty,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.03,1:09:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he went home a big hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.03,1:09:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace in our time.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.03,1:09:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And Hitler thought he was an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.41,1:09:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler thought Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.41,1:10:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,was really a dumbbell.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.37,1:10:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.37,1:10:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler thought, what an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.37,1:10:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamberlain walked out,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.37,1:10:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he went home a hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.37,1:10:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So he called up the troops,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.37,1:10:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,no opposition now,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.50,1:10:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you can see
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.50,1:10:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what went on with
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.92,1:10:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the League of Nations,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.92,1:10:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,did nothing really to stop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.92,1:10:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They could have stopped it very easily
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.92,1:10:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.92,1:10:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The attack on Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.92,1:10:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the London Blitz,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.17,1:10:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the Cambridge Five,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.17,1:10:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we see treason,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.27,1:10:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Ha Ha,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.27,1:10:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,traitors,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.27,1:10:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokyo Rose,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.27,1:10:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. McGonagall.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.27,1:10:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.33,1:10:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we're consciousness scientists
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.33,1:10:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,this afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.33,1:10:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.33,1:10:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you objectively
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.91,1:10:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,re-examine spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.91,1:10:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of the work I've done
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.91,1:10:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.91,1:11:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the verification of spiritual realities.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.92,1:11:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well you see
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.92,1:11:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there were the traitors
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.92,1:11:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.92,1:11:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the Cambridge Five,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.92,1:11:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.92,1:11:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,who gave the nuclear secrets
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.92,1:11:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to other countries,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.92,1:11:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,however they rationalized it,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.92,1:11:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they did,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.92,1:11:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and they crashed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.08,1:11:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do with the Iraqi War
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.08,1:11:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's very recent
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.24,1:11:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in people's mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.24,1:11:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and it may not be
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.24,1:11:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in accord with your belief system,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.24,1:11:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for which I apologize,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.24,1:11:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but the way to God, nobody said it was easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.24,1:11:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll explain
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.24,1:11:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,President Bush
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.24,1:11:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you don't have to say,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.24,1:11:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what about President Bush?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.50,1:11:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,President Bush,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.50,1:11:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I know his consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.50,1:11:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he took an oath,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.50,1:11:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact he told you,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.50,1:12:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I took an oath as President of the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.56,1:12:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to defend this country against all enemies,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.56,1:12:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is his prime commitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.56,1:12:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So when he puts his hand on a Bible,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.56,1:12:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he's a man who himself has evolved
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.56,1:12:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because of spiritual convictions,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.56,1:12:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when he puts his hand on a Bible
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.56,1:12:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that he will do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.56,1:12:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you know he will do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.56,1:12:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now how he does that,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.56,1:12:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you may not agree with,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.56,1:12:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but his intention is at 460,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.56,1:12:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so these people are all coming from about 450 or 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.56,1:12:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The U.S. Congress,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.72,1:12:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody in the U.S. population,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.72,1:12:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.72,1:12:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the intention was to,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.72,1:12:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.72,1:12:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.72,1:12:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the position of other
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.72,1:12:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,people at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.92,1:12:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.92,1:12:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,9-11,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.92,1:12:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to say,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.92,1:12:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we're rerunning what happened at 9-11,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.92,1:12:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Saddam Hussein,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.92,1:12:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Jihad,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.92,1:12:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Jihad is very dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.92,1:12:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Jihad at 50,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.98,1:12:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you better be scared of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.98,1:13:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jihad is real,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.04,1:13:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's really,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.04,1:13:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll explode or bomb anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.04,1:13:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the most dangerous person on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.04,1:13:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is a religious zealot,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.04,1:13:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a religious zealot is the most dangerous thing going,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.04,1:13:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like an atomic bomb on the loose,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.04,1:13:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.28,1:13:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,North Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.28,1:13:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't do North Korea recently,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.28,1:13:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we did North Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.28,1:13:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we were in Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.28,1:13:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to resolve the conflict,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.28,1:13:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at that time we were successful in 1999 I think,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.69,1:13:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time I think,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.69,1:13:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,let's just,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.69,1:13:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,do you want to do them,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.69,1:13:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if we have permission?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.30,1:13:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.30,1:13:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do the Koreas now
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.23,1:13:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of this audience,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.98,1:13:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.98,1:13:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd show it to you because you can see the practicality
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.66,1:13:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of the application of consciousness research in
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.28,1:14:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the everyday world and then the spiritual implications
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.90,1:14:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of this work as it reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.92,1:14:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,One more. What did you sing?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.44,1:14:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming out in a book that we're working on. Here we again
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.94,1:14:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,War and Peace. This is how we run quickly through a bunch of wars
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.10,1:14:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can see the usefulness. The Korean War, you see
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.12,1:14:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,where everybody was there. North Korea at that time was 80.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.08,1:14:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The communist regime was at 90. The U.S. position was
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.96,1:14:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,300. South Korea was 300. All those things have shifted since
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.18,1:14:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the time. At the time of the Korean War, this is how
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.86,1:14:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,things lined up. At the time of the Cold War
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.44,1:14:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you find out some interesting things.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.88,1:14:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,People accused the Vietnam War
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.88,1:15:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,veterans of faking it and all the Vietnam Syndrome, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.88,1:15:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We ask, was PTSD an actual clinical fact?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.88,1:15:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We get, yes, it is an actual clinical fact. We know many
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.91,1:15:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,people blown out by the Vietnam War who never recovered.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.91,1:15:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We see what the positions of everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.01,1:15:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,was at the time. Not too admirable on a
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.01,1:15:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,wide-scale viewpoint. During the Cold War, we see what the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.07,1:15:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,positions were. That was quite a few years, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.42,1:15:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither side comes out particularly
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.42,1:15:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,brilliantly. Neither the CIA, U.S. Intelligence,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.42,1:15:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,nor the Russian KGB.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.78,1:15:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,None of them come out to be very sterling kind of institutions.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.78,1:15:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Khrushchev and Brezhnev, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.81,1:15:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What went on in the Gulf War? We see President Bush, that was the elder,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.81,1:15:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,at 400, U.S. Military at 310.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.81,1:16:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Again we ask, Gulf War Syndrome, is that a fact or is that something
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.81,1:16:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,they just made up? The answer we got was that it was an actual
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.81,1:16:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,fact. Saddam Hussein calibrated at 95.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.10,1:16:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuwait at the time was 195.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.19,1:16:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,World War I, what went on? President Woodrow Wilson was 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.19,1:16:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And again we ask, was shell shock an actual clinical
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.19,1:16:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,fact? And the answer we get is yes. So the devastation
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.19,1:16:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of war on individual soldier is real. The Gulf War Syndrome,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.19,1:16:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Vietnam War Syndrome, shell shock after
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.19,1:16:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,World War I are actual facts. It's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.19,1:16:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In World War I, President Wilson was 400 and Kaiser Wilhelm
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.99,1:16:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was at 165. We thought for fun we'd go
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.34,1:16:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the Battle of Waterloo. And the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.34,1:16:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Waterloo, the Duke of Wellington was 405
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.34,1:17:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and Napoleon was 75.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.70,1:17:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're going to put your money out there, it would be nice to know these, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.70,1:17:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your money on the Duke of Wellington.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.70,1:17:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your money on the Duke of Wellington.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.70,1:17:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we invest then our energies and our efforts
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.70,1:17:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in line with that which is integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.73,1:17:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,With that which is integrous. Definably and verifiably
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.73,1:17:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous. Why? Because we say to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.89,1:17:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,ourselves, my own mind in and of itself is unable
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.89,1:17:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern truth from falsehood as clever as I think I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.89,1:17:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's mind thinks it's quite clever.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.86,1:17:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here who doesn't think his own mind is clever?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.17,1:17:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever your mind is. It was so clever nobody
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.39,1:17:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,answered, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.39,1:18:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the mind is extremely clever. Why is this? Because the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.06,1:18:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot survive unless it can convince you
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.10,1:18:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that it knows truth. If the ego knows
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.45,1:18:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, you don't need God. You understand that? The ego's
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.45,1:18:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,position then is to displace God.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.83,1:18:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To displace God. And to displace
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.31,1:18:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual souls with
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.98,1:18:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,egocentric ones. One thing we've gotten out of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.09,1:18:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,research then is a certain sense of humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.02,1:18:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain sense of humility. That as convincing as something may be
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.02,1:18:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,buttressed by centuries of argument, it can be
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.11,1:18:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,totally fallacious. What is the level of truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.40,1:18:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is something by which mankind has lived for a thousand years
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.40,1:19:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and you discover that it's only 160.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.50,1:19:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,People sacrifice their lives
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.52,1:19:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,by the millions for that which is not even
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.68,1:19:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,true. By the millions people sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.68,1:19:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,their lives for falsehood and illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.84,1:19:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the first generation, we're the first generation
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.84,1:19:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that's had a shot at truth. You realize that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.51,1:19:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had the good luck to be a pal of Jesus Christ
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.51,1:19:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,2003 years ago, you got a shot at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.51,1:19:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know how many people were within the province of his
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.24,1:19:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,teachings, within the purview of the Buddha or Jesus
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.24,1:19:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or any of the great teachers. Of course, the Vedas have
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.27,1:19:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,been a source of extremely high truth
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.27,1:19:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for close to 10,000 years, but they don't read the
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.52,1:20:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Vedas in Chicago or Cincinnati
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.52,1:20:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or London or any place else. You see, when
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.52,1:20:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth did come about by virtue of the inner awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.52,1:20:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of some mystic who sometimes got burned at the stake for his
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.52,1:20:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,efforts, it still only
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.52,1:20:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,had a local kind of an effect. It only had a local kind of effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.52,1:20:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I'm saying? So, you
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.51,1:20:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to become very compassionate about the human condition
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.51,1:20:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,itself. Born without fur or hooves
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.74,1:20:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or claws or fangs, no way to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.77,1:20:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you take this human being and put it out with
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.73,1:20:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,no clothes, nothing on, in the middle of woods, how is
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.73,1:20:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,he going to survive? So, you develop compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.08,1:20:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for the human condition, that it does whatever it thinks it has to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.08,1:21:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,do to survive, because that's been the nature of life since it's
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.08,1:21:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,been on the planet as it evolved, was first
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.08,1:21:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and foremost dedication to one's own survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.11,1:21:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, the extrapolation of that orientation
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.11,1:21:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as it expresses itself in mind. So, the maps that we just looked at
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.11,1:21:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,then, are the expression of the animal
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.11,1:21:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,nature as it evolved over the course of time, expressing
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.11,1:21:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,itself in the intellect, then in politics.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.11,1:21:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all the maps were within the expression
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.69,1:21:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of the primitive animal, how it expresses itself
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.69,1:21:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,politically. You see, the animal nature then
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.69,1:21:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,dominating whole continents. Whole continents
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.69,1:21:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate 70, 130, 140, 150,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.69,1:21:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,160, less than John Dillinger.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.03,1:22:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you now develop a compassion, because you see
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.50,1:22:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that which Jesus Christ and the Buddha both taught,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.66,1:22:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is only ignorance, that there is only ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.66,1:22:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And Krishna, of the great avatars of all history,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.62,1:22:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,stand for compassion, stand for forgiveness, stand that the only
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.62,1:22:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,sin possible is coming out of ignorance. Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.85,1:22:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,our generation somehow, now
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.17,1:22:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at 207, we have come into a different dominion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.17,1:22:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of consciousness at 207, we live in a different
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.55,1:22:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,world than our parents. We live in a different world
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.03,1:22:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,than we ourselves lived in until very recently. Our
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.38,1:22:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations of our self have shifted. And spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.38,1:22:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,curiosity, spiritual education
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.42,1:22:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,has becoming more and more dominant in our society. The interest in
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.42,1:23:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual issues is now quite strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.42,1:23:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In the same time, we've seen the emergence of
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.22,1:23:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,basically purely spiritual, not religious, but purely spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.22,1:23:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,teachings reaching the core of society.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.22,1:23:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the 12 steps of
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.28,1:23:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what started out as AA, now it's the 12 step program which covers
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.28,1:23:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,just about every human condition. You see, the 12 steps have
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.28,1:23:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,leaked out and pervade all of society. I hear many people on TV
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.28,1:23:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll pull out a phrase and I know exactly that they've been in AA or they got it there.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.28,1:23:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It came right to me, it got out of the 12 steps and the 12 traditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.28,1:23:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And then that leads into A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.79,1:23:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see an evolution of, you see 12 step psychology
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.79,1:23:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and thinking that's pervading business and society
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.79,1:23:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in many non-visible ways. Then you see
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.05,1:23:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,going on to the Course in Miracles and you see forgiveness and
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.05,1:24:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,how to recontextualize things so that you see them differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.17,1:24:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to transcend the polarity of the opposites, the way to
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.17,1:24:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend guilt and anger and hatred of others
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.61,1:24:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is by recontextualization. That a thing looks
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.63,1:24:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,different when it's recontextualized is beginning to emerge in society.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.63,1:24:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,See, people don't realize that we're having a profound effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.63,1:24:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,On the news now you hear the word
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.63,1:24:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,perceived. Perceived. See, that perception
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.69,1:24:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is one thing and reality is another. The police
